{
  "texts": [
    "Weekly log data were employed by the LSTM model to transform the performance prediction into a time-series classification issue for early prediction.",
    "In addition, the study has used a shapely additive explanation model to determine the key indicators of student retention, such as quiz attempts and assessment submissions.",
    "In comparison to all other options, the deep LSTM exhibited the strongest predictive power to distinguish between pass and fail students, reaching an accuracy of 84.57%, a precision of 82.24%, and a recall of 79.43%.",
    "A study by Al-Zawqari et al (2022), used Random Forests (RFs) and Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) to predict student's academic performance without feature engineering and attempted to reduce flexibility.",
    "Throughout the first quarter of the course, the midterm, the third quarter of the course, and two weeks before the course's end, this include four distinct binary classification problems (Distinction, Pass, Fail, and Withdrawn) were developed using the OULA dataset to test the proposed model."
  ]
}